# Printer Rescue - Test Cases (v1)

1) User can choose a brand (HP/Canon/Lexmark/Brother)  
Expected: brand selects and next step shows.

2) User can start “Find IP address” guide  
Expected: guide opens with simple steps.

3) IP field accepts a valid IP like 192.168.1.25  
Expected: no error, continue.

4) IP field rejects invalid IP like 999.1.1.1  
Expected: shows clear error message.

5) App handles “I don’t know my printer model”  
Expected: shows generic instructions (no dead end).

6) App handles “printer has no display”  
Expected: gives button-based instructions.

7) App handles APIPA IP 169.254.x.x  
Expected: warns it’s likely not on network + next steps.

8) App generates a ticket summary with brand + IP  
Expected: summary is readable and has copy button.
